MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience developing, analyzing, and selecting appropriate information and presenting the information in a form and at a level suitable for the intended audience equivalent to the GS-11 grade level or pay band in the federal service, or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate performing the duties such as: 1.) Producing creative, informative, and readable media products;
2.) Creating visually appealing web content that is attractive and effective using software such as Adobe Creative Suite, Photoshop, and SharePoint;
3.) Interviewing subjects who are sometimes reluctant to share information;
4.) Analyzing data and research in order to produce strategic marketing content, communicating risk management information;
5.) Engaging contributing writers and technical advisors in identifying the needs of magazine readers, web visitors, or any other audience. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management web site: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills and can provide valuable training and experience that translates directly to paid employment.
